torsmo: System Monitor for Linux
torsmo: 
torsmo: Torsmo is a system monitor for Linux that sits in the corner of your
torsmo: desktop. Torsmo renders itself on the root window (on the desktop) or
torsmo: to its own transparent window any special eyecandy.  Among other
torsmo: things, it can display information about your kernel version, uptime,
torsmo: system time, NIC info, hostname, temperatures, battery info, process
torsmo: information, local mail, and filesystem statistics.
torsmo: 
torsmo: Homepage: http://torsmo.sourceforge.net/
torsmo: 
